{"title":"Randomized firm parameters with asymmetric information","markdown":{"headingText":"Randomized firm parameters with asymmetric information","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"::: {.question}\n\n**Share Repurchase and Market Value Impact (Asymmetric Information)**\n\n```{r}\n#| eval: true\n#| results: asis\n#| echo: false\n#| warning: false\n\nset.seed(908)\nlibrary(webexercises)\nlibrary(knitr)\n\nshares_outstanding <- round(rnorm(1, mean = 60, sd = 5), 2)  # random number of shares outstanding (million)\nstock_price <- round(rnorm(1, mean = 26, sd = 3), 2)  # random price per share (dollars)\nmarket_belief <- round(rnorm(1, mean = 1550, sd = 100), 2)  # market belief in firm value (million)\ntrue_value <- round(rnorm(1, mean = 1600, sd = 120), 2)  # true firm value (million)\nrepurchase_amount <- round(rnorm(1, mean = 105, sd = 5), 2)  # random repurchase amount (million dollars)\n\n# Price calculations\nshares_repurchased <- round(repurchase_amount / stock_price, 2)  # shares repurchased in millions\nshares_remaining <- round(shares_outstanding - shares_repurchased, 2)  # shares outstanding after repurchase\n```\n\n\nGamma Corp. has `r shares_outstanding` million shares outstanding, and its stock is currently trading at `r stock_price` per share. The true value of the firm is `r true_value` million, but the market believes it is worth `r market_belief` million. The company plans to repurchase `r repurchase_amount` million worth of its own shares. Calculate: (a) the number of shares repurchased; and (b) the number of shares outstanding after the repurchase.\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center;\"> <label for=\"module10_num_q3a_single\"><strong>a. Shares repurchased (millions):</strong></label> <input type=\"number\" id=\"module10_num_q3a_single\" name=\"module10_num_q3a_single\" style=\"width:160px;\" data-correct-answer=`r shares_repurchased` data-tolerance=\"0.1\" step=\"0.01\" /> </form> <div id=\"feedback-module10_num_q3a_single\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\"> ✅ Shares repurchased = Repurchase amount / Stock price = `r repurchase_amount` / `r stock_price` = <b>`r shares_repurchased`M</b>. </div>\n:::\n::: {.question-block}\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center;\"> <label for=\"module10_num_q3b_single\"><strong>b. Shares outstanding after repurchase (millions):</strong></label> <input type=\"number\" id=\"module10_num_q3b_single\" name=\"module10_num_q3b_single\" style=\"width:160px;\" data-correct-answer=`r shares_remaining` data-tolerance=\"0.1\" step=\"0.01\" /> </form> <div id=\"feedback-module10_num_q3b_single\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\"> ✅ Shares outstanding after repurchase = Shares outstanding - Shares repurchased = `r shares_outstanding` - `r shares_repurchased` = <b>`r shares_remaining`M</b>. </div>\n:::\n:::","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"knitr"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":